# autostart.txt -- programs started automatically at boot, one per line.
#
# Each line is a shell command, run like in the terminal: the first word is a /bin
# tool (/bin/<word>.elf) and the rest are its arguments. Launch a DESKTOP app with
# the `run` tool. Blank lines and '#' comments are ignored.
#
#   run shell     -> launches apps/shell.app/main.elf (the activity shell)
#   keyb FR       -> /bin/keyb.elf FR      -> set the French keyboard layout
#
# The activity shell owns the whole screen (its own background + top/timeline bars).
# voronoy generates the wallpaper then EXITS; it also serves as the 2nd boot app that
# masks a pre-existing single-GUI-app-at-boot race (so keep it before the shell).
run voronoy
run shell
keyb FR
